addModule(address,address).details: Add a compliance module for a token Can be called by owner (for any token) or by the token itself

canTransfer(address,address,uint256).details: Check if a transfer is compliant with all modules

returns._0: bool True if compliant with ALL modules

created(address,uint256).details: Called when tokens are created (minted) - notify all modules

destroyed(address,uint256).details: Called when tokens are destroyed (burned) - notify all modules

params.from: Address from which tokens are burned

getModuleAt(address,uint256).details: Get module at specific index for a token

getModuleCount(address).details: Get number of modules for a token

getModules(address).details: Get all compliance modules for a token

getTokenCount().details: Get number of tokens using this aggregator

getTokens().details: Get all tokens using this aggregator

isModuleActiveForToken(address,address).details: Check if a module is active for a token

isTokenRegistered(address).details: Check if a token is registered

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeModule(address,address).details: Remove a compliance module from a token Can be called by owner (for any token) or by the token itself

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

transferred(address,address,uint256).details: Called when a transfer occurs - notify all modules
